    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make catcalling and street harassment a punishable offence.",
        "additional_details": "Campaigns such as Catcalls of London: http://bit.ly/catcallsofldn \r\nhelp to highlight the extent of the problem, as does Hollaback!, Stop Street Harassment and Safe and the City to name a few.\r\nOut of 3000 submissions of stories I have received 72% were under 17, 60% were wearing a school uniform, and 100% of the perpetrators were adults males. \r\nFrance imposed first fine for street harassment last year: \r\nhttps://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-45643864\r\nand Belgium, Portugal, New Zealand all have legislation in place.",
        "background": "We all have the right to feeling safe in public spaces. If street harassment is criminalized this could reduce the number of incidents of non-consensual touching and unsolicited sexual attention experienced in public. France, Portugal, and Belgium all have legislation in place, so why don't we?",
